<!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
<section class="faq-section" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header reveal">
      <div class="section-label">\u2753 FAQ</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently asked <span class="gradient-text">questions</span></h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          How do I get Captions?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Captions is available on iOS (App Store), Android (Google Play), and on the web at captions.ai. Download the app for the best mobile experience, or use the web version for desktop editing with your browser.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          Is Captions free to use?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Captions is free to download and includes basic editing tools. To unlock AI editing, avatar creation, 100+ caption templates, and all generative features, you'll want a Pro, Max, or Scale plan. You can explore plans starting at $9.99/month.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          What languages does Captions support?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Captions generates auto-captions in 100+ languages with high accuracy. The AI translation and lip-dub feature supports dubbing into 30+ languages, allowing you to reach a global audience without re-recording your content.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          How does the AI editing work?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Simply upload your video and pick a style. Captions' AI analyzes your footage, cuts scenes intelligently, adds B-roll, syncs music, applies transitions, and generates captions \u2014 all automatically. The whole process takes under 2 minutes.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          Can I switch plans at any time?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Yes! You can upgrade or downgrade at any time from your account settings. Upgrades take effect immediately with prorated billing. Downgrades remain active until the end of your current billing cycle. No hidden fees or penalties.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          Do AI credits expire?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Unused credits roll over to the next month. Your balance can hold up to 3x your monthly allowance \u2014 so up to two months of unused credits are saved for you. This means you can bank credits during slow months and use them when you need to produce more.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          What video formats are supported?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Captions supports all major formats including MP4, MOV, AVI, MKV, and WEBM. You can import vertical (9:16) and horizontal (16:9) videos, up to 4K resolution. Export options include all major social media aspect ratios.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">
          Is there an Enterprise plan?
          <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">Yes! Enterprise plans include custom pricing, bulk credit discounts, dedicated account management, priority support, custom onboarding, and training data exclusion. Contact our sales team to build a custom package for your organization.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

